<span id="ix.cxix-p3"></span>*To Jovinus, Bishop of Perrha*. <span
id="fr_2393"></span>[2394](#fn_2393.md)

<span id="ix.cxix-p5"></span><span class="c14"><span
id="ix.cxix-p5.1"></span>You</span> owe me a good turn.  For I lent you
a kindness, which I ought to get back with interest;—a kind of interest,
this, which our Lord does not refuse.  Pay me, then, my friend, by
paying me a visit.  So much for the capital; what of the increment?  It
is the fact of the visit being paid by you, who are a man as much
superior to me, as fathers are better than children.

